'''''The Dark Knight''''' is a 2008 superhero film directed, produced, and co-written by [[Christopher Nolan]]. Based on the [[DC Comics]] character [[Batman]], the film is the second installment of Nolan's ''[[The Dark Knight Trilogy]]'' and a sequel to 2005's ''[[Batman Begins]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Dark Knight (2008)|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=darkknight.htm|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=July 17, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Krenn|first=Michael|title=Batman in the Movies|publisher=DK Publishing|year=2009|isbn=978-0-7566-4483-6}}</ref> The movie stars [[Christian Bale]] as Batman, [[Heath Ledger]] as the Joker and [[Aaron Eckhart]] as Harvey Dent/Two-Face. It is a follow-up to 2005's ''[[Batman Begins]]'' and was followed by 2012's ''[[The Dark Knight Rises]]''.
